Number2  = 11\n| Title           = Songwriting & Starfish\n| DirectedBy      = Eric Dean Seaton\n| WrittenBy       = Eric Friedman\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2012|3|11}}\n| ProdCode        = 110\n| Viewers         = 2.63<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2012/03/13/sundays-cable-ratings-walking-dead-still-unstoppable-for-amc-542412/cable_20120311/|title=Sunday's Cable Ratings|publisher=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=March 13, 2012|access-date=December 12, 2017}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Austin is interested in participating in the Hot Summer Jam Contest, with a little help from his friends. The contest takes place at the beach where Ally wants to get over her bad memories so she and Austin can work out some lyrics. When Ally's book gets covered in gum, Trish puts the book into her cart to freeze the gum so they can scrape it off. They forget about the book and have to try and break into the shop to get it back. While in the shop they get locked in the freezer, so Austin calls Dez to save them. Dez finally rescues them, but they get caught by Officer Dunphy. While in the police station, they explain the story, and Officer Dunphy accuses them of stealing Fruity Mint Swirl ice-cream in the shop's freezer, forcing them to miss the contest. While Officer Dunphy is filling out police reports, he shows that he is an amazing drummer. Austin invites him to be in his band at the contest, and convinces him to let them go.\n\n''Guest star'': [[Kelly Perine]] as Officer Dunphy\n| LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 12\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 12\n| Title           = Soups & Stars\n| DirectedBy      = [[Shannon Flynn (director)|Shannon Flynn]]\n| WrittenBy       = Wayne Conley\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2012|3|25}}\n| ProdCode        = 115\n| Viewers         = 2.58<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2012/03/28/sundays-cable-ratings-mad-men-leads-viewers-nba-tops-demos-155212/cable_20120325/|title=Sunday's Cable Ratings|publisher=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=March 28, 2012|access-date=December 12, 2017}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = <!-- Episode summaries must be expressed in your own words. Do NOT submit content you find from another web site as it is plagiarism and likely a copyright violation, which Wikipedia cannot accept and will be removed or reverted. Superficially modifying copyrighted content or closely paraphrasing it, even if the source is cited, still constitutes a copyright violation. Summaries should be about 100 to 200 words in length, per WP:TVPLOT, and those substantially less than 100 words are most likely to be scrutinized for possible copyright violation. -->\n\n''Guest star'': [[Lynne Marie Stewart]] as Miss Suzy\n| LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 13\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 13\n| Title           = Burglaries & Boobytraps\n| DirectedBy      = Shelley Jensen\n| WrittenBy       = Aaron Ho & Steve Freeman\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2012|4|15}}\n| ProdCode        = 106\n| Viewers         = 3.28<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2012/04/17/sundays-cable-ratings-game-of-thrones-win-streak-continues-736415/cable_20120415/|title=Sunday's Cable Ratings|publisher=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=April 17, 2012|access-date=December 20, 2017}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = When the stores in the mall start getting robbed, Ally and a team of other mall employees set out to find out who the burglar is. A security camera shows Austin taking a guitar from a display case at Sonic Boom. Austin later explains that he was trying to get the guitar autographed by [[Bruno Mars]], much to Ally and Trish's surprise. With most of the mall thinking that Austin is the culprit, the group must scramble to figure out who's really responsible. Meanwhile, a delivery worker delivers items to all stores including Sonic Boom, but his request for a [[Gratuity|tip]] goes unnoticed. The burglar turns out to be the delivery man after Austin hides in the piano that the burglar takes.\n\n''Guest stars'': Andy Milder as Lester, Greg Worswick as Billl<!-- not a typo, credit actually shows three L's in character's name -->\n| LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 14\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 14\n| Title           = myTAB & My Pet\n| DirectedBy      = Phill Lewis\n| WrittenBy       = Rick Nyholm\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2012|4|22}}\n| ProdCode        = 114\n| Viewers         = 2.87<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2012/04/24/sundays-cable-ratings-another-week-another-game-of-thrones-win-414203/cable_20120422/|title=Sunday's Cable Ratings|publisher=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=April 24, 2012|access-date=December 12, 2017}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = <!-- Episode summaries must be expressed in your own words. Do NOT submit content you find from another web site as it is plagiarism and likely a copyright violation, which Wikipedia cannot accept and will be removed or reverted. Superficially modifying copyrighted content or closely paraphrasing it, even if the source is cited, still constitutes a copyright violation. Summaries should be about 100 to 200 words in length, per WP:TVPLOT, and those substantially less than 100 words are most likely to be scrutinized for possible copyright violation. -->\n\n''Guest stars'': [[Ashley Fink]] as Mindy, Greg Worswick as Billl<!-- not a typo, credit actually shows three L's in character's name -->\n| LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 15\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 15\n| Title           = Filmmaking & Fear Breaking\n| DirectedBy      = Roger Christiansen\n| WrittenBy       = Rick Nyholm\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2012|5|20}}\n| ProdCode        = 112\n| Viewers         = 3.05<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2012/05/22/sundays-cable-ratings-spurs-clippers-best-thrones-kardashians-888110/cable_20120520/|title=Sunday's Cable Ratings|publisher=[[The Futon Critic]]|