  = Everglades & Allygators\n| DirectedBy      = Shelley Jensen\n| WrittenBy       = Clay Lapari\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2012|7|15}}\n| ProdCode        = 119\n| Viewers         = 3.52<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2012/07/17/sundays-cable-ratings-hbos-true-blood-holds-off-scripted-premieres-258111/cable_20120715/|title=Sunday's Cable Ratings|publisher=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=July 17, 2012|access-date=December 20, 2017}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Shiny Money invites Austin and the group to his annual Swamp Blast party in the [[Everglades]]. When they get there, the power in the houseboat goes out. Meanwhile, Trish and Dez go out to hunt for a legendary [[alligator]], \"Big Mama\". Little do they know, a baby alligator followed them to the boat, attracting Big Mama. Big Mama bursts through the boat door, but the group works together and makes her leave. Dez accidentally drills a hole in the floor of the boat, causing it to sink. In the end, Austin delivers an unforgettable performance at the Swamp Blast.\n\n''Guest stars'': James Earl as Shiny Money, John Lee Ames as Clavis\n| LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 18\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 18\n| Title           = Successes & Setbacks\n| DirectedBy      = Shelley Jensen\n| WrittenBy       = Samantha Silver & Joey Manderino\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2012|8|19}}\n| ProdCode        = 117\n| Viewers         = 3.29<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2012/08/21/sundays-cable-ratings-hbos-true-blood-goes-untouched-once-again-539013/cable_20120819/|title=Sunday's Cable Ratings|publisher=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=August 21, 2012|access-date=December 20, 2017}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = <!-- Episode summaries must be expressed in your own words. Do NOT submit content you find from another web site as it is plagiarism and likely a copyright violation, which Wikipedia cannot accept and will be removed or reverted. Superficially modifyi