cast-finals-no-stopping-the-nfl-walking-dead-37115/cable_20131110/|title=Sunday's Cable Ratings & Broadcast Finals|publisher=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=November 12, 2013|access-date=December 20, 2017}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = In Washington D.C., the last stop of Austin's tour, Austin receives a \"Role Model of the Year\" award, which makes Dez so desperate to get one as well since he hasn't received an award in his life before. Afterward, the group does some sightseeing at a [[List of Smithsonian museums|Smithsonian Museum]]. While Ally impresses herself as an amateur tour guide, Austin tries on some movie memorabilia and inadvertently gets his feet stuck in a pair of Dorothy's silver shoes. The group is able to elude museum security. Trish receives a call confirming that Austin will perform for the president of the United States. During his performance, Austin wears huge sneakers, but one of them slips off and nearly hits the president. Austin comes clean and tells the president the truth, who is moved by his honesty and pardons him. The president then awards Dez a medal for blocking the sneaker that was about to hit him.\n\n''Guest stars'': Tom Fonss as Anders, [[Reggie Brown (impersonator)|Reggie Brown]] as President<!-- this is how he is credited; do not add in which President of the U.S. he impersonates -->\n| LineColor       = A52A2A\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 49\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n| Title           = Beach Clubs & BFFs\n| DirectedBy      = Sean Lambert\n| WrittenBy       = Samantha Silver & Joey Manderino\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2013|11|24}}\n| ProdCode        = 304\n| Viewers         = 3.09<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2013/11/26/sundays-cable-ratings-and-broadcast-finals-nfl-coverage-puts-fox-nbc-on-top-749411/cable_20131124/|title=Sunday's Cable Ratings & Broadcast Finals|publisher=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=November 26, 2013|access-date=December 20, 2017}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = <!-- Episode su